briefTitle: Study to Evaluate the Immunogenicity and Safety of GlaxoSmithKline (GSK) Biologicals' Quadrivalent Influenza Vaccine (GSK2282512A) Compared to Fluzone® Quadrivalent in Children 6 to 35 Months of Age
officialTitle: Immunogenicity and Safety Study of GSK Biologicals' Quadrivalent Influenza Vaccine (GSK2282512A) Compared to Fluzone® Quadrivalent in Children 6 to 35 Months of Age
summary: The purpose of this study is to assess the immunogenicity and safety of GSK Biologicals' quadrivalent influenza vaccine (GSK2282512A) compared to Sanofi Pasteur's Fluzone® Quadrivalent in children 6 to 35 months of age.

primaryOutcome.measure: Haemagglutination Inhibition (HI) Antibody Titers Against Each of the 4 Vaccine Influenza Strains
primaryOutcome.timeFrame: 28 days after last vaccine dose (i.e. Day 28 for vaccine-primed subjects and Day 56 for vaccine-unprimed subjects)
